 The Causal Compression (\mathbf{K_C}) Equation
The fundamental premise of \mathbf{K_C} is that the most direct and necessary path for a system's evolution or action (Time \mathbf{T}) is achieved through the maximum possible compression of its infinite computational possibilities.
